<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <persName type="from">President</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">King of England</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Mansion</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-22"><hi rend="italic">January 22,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have received with profound sorrow the lamentable tidings of the death
                            of Her Majesty the Queen. Allow me, sir, to offer my sincere sympathy
                            and that of the American people in your personal bereavement and in the
                            loss Great Britain has suffered in the death of its venerable and
                            illustrious sovereign, whose noble life and beneficent influence have
                            promoted the peace and won the affection of the world.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                            McKinley.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>